AGI - "In recent months I have repeatedly urged all political leaders to sign an agreement not to apply for Europeans. Schlein and Tajani have already chosen the path of direct application. But the descent into the field of the President of the Council and its anti-European and sovereign platform, completely change the scenario. We must oppose with all the means to the project of 'a small Italy in a small Europa&nbsp; by Giorgia Meloni". So, in a note, the leader of Action, Carlo Calenda.
&nbsp;
"It is necessary to respond to this anti-European challenge by putting itself into play," adds Calenda, who then points out: "After consulting the party director, Elena Bonetti and I decided to accept the challenge and apply together in all the constituencies to give even more strength to the team of extraordinary quality that we have put in the field for weeks, with a clear and clear program and the obligation for all candidates to join the Renew group. We are European and will prove it on June 8th and 9th." &nbsp;

