AGI - "I never said that disabled children and boys should be in classes separated from others. I said that they must be together with other children and boys but that they would need special commitments and also suitable and dedicated facilities for special attention moments aimed at their disability. Exactly what many parents with disabled children would like to do but unfortunately these facilities are very few and waiting lists are very long". General Roberto Vannacci, independent candidate on the League's lists for Europeans at Affaritaliani.it.
&nbsp;
"Just re-read my statements to realize how much I wanted to express, also citing the need for specialists to specifically deal with disability. Unfortunately, there is the misconception, by a certain press, of making high-sounding titles that exult from the words expressed in the interview with the precise purpose of demonising the interlocutor and of distorting the thoughts expressed", he adds. As for the criticism of many members of the League, such as the Minister of Economy Giancarlo Giorgetti, "they are internal diatribes to the party that I consider more than legitimate but that I do not care. I have an idea of tradition, of homeland, of culture and sovereignty very similar to that of the League and that I will carry on independently."
&nbsp;
The criticisms did not annoy him, "are internal discussions that do not concern me. The problem will be solved by the vote of the citizens, if they vote for me I will be elected otherwise I will do more. I would like to thank Mr Salvini for the opportunity to apply for me. With the secretary of the League there were no contracts, as someone states, but talks and interlocutions culminated on April 25 with the announcement by Salvini of my independent candidacy in the League lists".&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<a href="https://www.agi.it/politica/news/2024-04-27/classes-separate-per-disabili-polemica-interview-general-vannacci-26185935/"> The storm broke out after an interview by the general at the press. Vannacci had expressed some beliefs ("the Italian has white skin, the statistics say it"; the homosexual who "supported by exhibitionist must accept criticism"; "Abortion is not a right"; students at school, including the disabled "are divided according to their abilities") welcomed with frost by the Minister of Economy, Giancarlo Giorgetti.&nbsp;
Roberto Vannacci "is not of the League", said Giorgetti in Varese on the margin of the event in support of the candidacy for Europeans, in the lists of the League, of Isabella Tovaglieri.
<h2>Russian: on school and handicapped
"If he had a child with a handicap, or had a nephew with a handicap, he would have understood that he had said a nonsense," said the President of the Senate, Ignatius Russian, during the public interview with the FdI programme conference.
<h2> A disabled childhood friend, "helps are specific"</h2>
General Roberto Vannacci "with fearful humility declares himself unknowing to these problems, expressing with a direct analysis, courageous and of great reality, the delicate subject of disability: with these words a disabled childhood friend of the candidate for the Europeans, Norberto De Angelis, defended Vannacci's words on the disabled in a letter that the AGI could see. Vannacci "is unequivocally direct and clear when he exalts and does not denigrate the category (of the disabled, ndr) and I am sure he does it of heart, because he is always with the heart that welcomed me in his house near his two daughters". "When we talk about disability, what kind did you address? Disable motor or mental or intellectual or sensory? Disable from birth or post-mortem or post-trauma?", continues De Angelis, "you know well that the word itself contains myriads of diversity, educational treatments, school teaching, medical, psychological" and more. "If on the one hand social life, especially in schools, and friendship between individuals without pathologies with disabled people helps knowledge about how to relate to them and therefore as adults will have greater concern and respect", he notes, "it is also true that the ability to learn mental disabilities, have dynamics all of them and too subjective. Let's not hide behind a finger or pretend moralists."
<h2> Mule (FI), on the disabled, an offensive fesserie
"General&nbsp;Vannacci&nbsp; said a solemn festive, but seriously offensive: It's a thought you'll never find citizenship in those who adhere to Forza Italia. We are the ones that we put to the index, labeling them as shameful and as a turnaround, the arguments made by the extreme right-wing German party Afd on the disabled at school completely superimposed to those of&nbsp;Vannacci". Giorgio Mule', Vice-President of the Chamber and Member of Forza Italia, said this by speaking to Sky tg24. "A delicate and indeed very delicate theme like disability - he added - demands knowledge, deepening, respect and therefore does not face with superficiality or worse with a joke.&nbsp; Vannacci, as far as I'm concerned and much before this last scheduling, in the class of politics was already ideally behind the board. "The election campaigns, however, serve this: who goes to vote - concludes Mule' - must express a preference on the person, so it is good that he knows the candidates because if you know them you can also avoid them." &nbsp;
<h2>Brambilla (Nm-Maie), ask for an apology to all Italians
"General&nbsp;Vannacci&nbsp; should apologize, first of all, to children and children with disabilities, to their families and then to all Italians. If you realize the society you imagine, we'd all live in a nightmare. Discrimination is not an instrument of government, but the product of nineteenth-century ideologies which in the last century have already provoked unrest." Michela Vittoria Brambilla (Nm-Maie), chairman of the parliamentary committee for childhood and adolescence. "Even net of the clarifications and half marches back - warns the deputation of We moderates - it is a simply intolerable idea. Modern pedagogy says more and inclusion is a generally shared goal. Exclusion &nbsp;Vannacci, is meant. How could the League, which expresses the Minister for Disability, nominate the general, supporter of a sort of school apartheid? Not by chance, let's talk about plural disability. Disability is a lot different. But all those who bear it must face daily challenges, from architectural barriers to the variety of prejudices. The answer can't be ghettoization since childhood, it would mean returning to a past now handed over to the archive. On the contrary: our children must grow together and support the children who have special needs, with adequate investments and people formed for the purpose. From a candidate to the European Parliament we would expect a commitment in this direction."
<h2>Sbrollini, also in Veneto discomfort for the choices of Salvini&nbsp;></h2>
"After the umpteenth series of shoots yesterday, not least the one on the separate classes for disabled children, the ill-noise between colleagues and the base for the candidacy of&nbsp; Vannacci&nbsp; it is increasingly palpable and widespread." It says Daniela Sbrollini, senator of Italia Viva. "The discomfort for the choices of Matteo&nbsp;Salvini&nbsp; seems to save no political level. In the open disappointment of the president of Friuli-Venezia-Giulia Fedriga and the vice-president of the Centinaio Senate, a similar dissatisfaction is reflected in the territories. In Vicenza, for example, the growing insophagus per&nbsp;Vannacci&nbsp; is now evident. To demonstrate that even in Veneto the consent per&nbsp;Salvini&nbsp;is sinking. That this, also complicit in the failure to grant to Zaia by the government of the third mandate, happens in a historically loyalist land, opens interesting perspectives for reformist parties like the United States of Europe. There are all the conditions for a change in the political landscape," he concludes.
<h2>Cateno De Luca, pathetic, is poisoned apple per&nbsp;Salvini&nbsp;></h2>
"I read this morning the pathetic reconstruction of General&nbsp; Vannacci&nbsp; to try to get out of the embarrassment towards the League after some background of his relationship with me emerged. He says that he was approached by my sgherri, but it is up to me to deny it and tell that I was approached on his behalf by very respectable people and some of the same rank of the general."&nbsp; The South leader says that he calls the North and the Federator of the Liberta' Cateno De Luca list, adding: "The hypothesis of a meeting with him I said no, because his 'non-ideas' are far from my political history and from my human sensibility. I've always fought disparities, and I've always been next to those who are ghettoized for their diversity, shoving me against the vari&nbsp;Vannacci. Today in the light of what happened in the 48 hours after the formalization of his candidacy in the League I can say that I did a good job having contributed to the acceptance of much of the mad conditions put by the&nbsp;Vannacci&nbsp;to Matteo&nbsp;Salvini. I have done everything so that'&nbsp;Vannacci&nbsp;it became the poisoned apple of Matteo&nbsp;Salvini&nbsp;exposing me with interlocution and predisposition of symbols to feed the 'political megalomania of the&nbsp;Vannacci&nbsp;thought'. I knew from some of my authoritative contacts within the League that treated it with&nbsp; Vannacci&nbsp; he was argued for his claim to have a reference in the symbol and the candidacy in all the colleges as a leader. I've been at the game, and I've been focusing on the authoritative intermediaries to do early because anyway I was depositing the symbol and closing the lists for how it actually was. I did this job not for the &nbsp;Vannacci&nbsp; but to further highlight the disturbing political personality of Matteo&nbsp;Salvini, now increasingly a boxer played in derby with Forza Italia. I was certain that within the League no one wanted to&nbsp; Vannacci&nbsp; and in fact all deny it, especially the base that made the League great. Now I expect from the real leghists a real 'vaffa' inside the urn. Good election campaign Matteo! Continue like this...".&nbsp;
<h2>Savine, from him serious words on the disabled
"To campaign, in search of an extra vote, you can't legitimize a concept of society where there are no rights, or worse, where rights exist only for those who like it or join us. This has nothing to do with freedom of opinion, but it's offensive to the history and culture of our country. Also for this reason, the words of Roberto&nbsp;Vannacci, who still dresses a uniform, on the disabled are particularly serious and offensive. Our society must do everything necessary to continue to break down those barriers that have existed for too many decades, enhancing social services to support the autonomy of people with disabilities and their families, not to go back, creating new ghettos." This was said by the undersecretary to the Ministry of Economy and Finance, and regional secretary of Forza Italia in Friuli Venezia Giulia, Sandra Savino.&nbsp;

