AGI - It is dark on the statements of General Roberto Vannacci, candidate for the League in European elections. In an interview with the Press Vannacci he expressed some convictions ("Italian has white skin, says statistics"; the homosexual who "supported by exhibitionist must accept criticism"; "Abortion is not a right"; students at school, including the disabled "are divided according to their abilities") welcomed with frost by the Minister of Economy, Giancarlo Giorgetti.
Roberto Vannacci "is not of the League", said Giorgetti in Varese on the margin of the event in support of the candidacy to Europeans, in the lists of the League, of Isabella Tovaglieri. The latter, he observed the owner of the Dicastery of Economy, "is a daughter of this land, hears what people think, serves the territory". To the chroniclers who pointed out that Vannacci is not, he replied: "Right phrase and already contains the answer." Finally, on Vannacci's declarations, Giorgetti has replied dryly: "I don't share."
&nbsp;
I also have the vice-president of Cei, Monsignor Francesco Savino: "The separate classes breed ghettos. Instead our disabled brothers have so many skills that we do not have. Please we are serious and we are responsible - it has concluded the prelate - avoiding returns to dark years". To the controversies General Vannacci has replicated &nbsp;> with a statement to AGI: "The diversity of disabled people must be valued in the best way, allowing them to express themselves and realize themselves fully by following their talents. For the disabled they invented the paralympics, they did not put them to run with those disabled is not. My childhood friend Norberto De Angelis is a champion of disability: he is in the wheelchair for a road accident, but he has won several paralympic races training in a peculiar way and making it stand out through his diversity as best he could express." The general explained: "For this yesterday, in the interview, after specifying not to be a disability expert, I said to be convinced that the disabled should be helped in the most peculiar and specific way possible. Which, sometimes, may not coincide with putting them together with other people with different characteristics." As for the phrases on Benito Mussolini,&nbsp;Vannacci, he claimed: "is a statist, like Stalin, because they are "statemen&nbsp; as Treccani writes."
&nbsp;
Needless to say that Vannacci's statements have recompacted the opposition.&nbsp; "In the incredible words of the general on the separate classes for disabled children echo concepts in vogue during a historical period called Nazism", he said&nbsp;Raffaella Paita>, senator and national coordinator of Italia Viva. "With its chilling &nbsp exit; Vannacci&nbsp; has crossed a line that must never be exceeded. We ask the ministra della Disability Locatelli to immediately distance itself from such horror."&nbsp; The same concept reiterated also&nbsp;Davide Faraone, leader of Italia Viva alla Camera: "The party expressing the disability minister is the same as the European candidate general&nbsp; Vannacci&nbsp;which today offers special classes for girls and boys with disabilities. And to maintain high his racist profile feeling that Italians have white skin and that Mussolini is a statist. This is the League of Matteo&nbsp;Salvini&nbsp; which will prepare for the European elections. The ministra Locatelli distances itself from such absurdity," concluded Pharaoh.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"The words of Vannacci&nbsp; on the separate classes for disabled students - they have emphasized&nbsp; the M5S exponents in cultural committee> - are delusional, dangerous or offensive for thousands of families. The Legislative candidate propagates an inhuman ghettoization of children, in contrast to the deepest values of our Constitution and with the United Nations Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities, which commits to equal participation of persons with disabilities in society, school of course included. What do Leghisti ministers think of disability and education Alessandra Locatelli and Giuseppe Valditara? They will defend the Italian public school and students disabled by the deliri di&nbsp; Vannacci&nbsp; or will the idea of bringing back to the darkest and terrible years of the last century?" &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"So Vannacci&nbsp; he is a candidate. I made a comparison with him a few weeks ago.&nbsp; Vannacci&nbsp; it was very good for &nbsp;Salvini. It's all and nothing, I'm marketing and badge," said Azione's leader, Carlo Calenda>.&nbsp; "Here's a general running for the Europeans - is the analysis of &nbsp;Arturo Scotto, a Democratic Party congressman -.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ed has a vast program. Rehabilitate Mussolini because a great statist. Introduce different classes for disabled children. To certify the nation's white identity. I don't think you're joking. His is a vast program. I never use the word randomly: but the smell of fascism feels a mile away. With good peace of the minimizers. The prevailing figure or the cowardice or complicity." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"Everyone today speaks of &nbsp;Vannacci&nbsp; and its shameful phrases on the disabled. The general provokes, others replicate. I am proud and proud to have signed the law on after us, on autistic spectrum disorders, on the third sector. The others - he said&nbsp;&nbsp;Matteo&nbsp;Renzi, > leader of Iv - are divided among those who provoke and who chat: we are those of the laws of social rights." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
For the president of the Italian Paralympic Committee, Luca&nbsp;Pancalli, > that of the separate classes for the disabled, "is&nbsp; an unacceptable and retriva proposal, fortunately the society is ahead. The Italian school first in Europe, in 1976, abolished the differential classes favouring a full inclusion of pupils and disabled pupils giving them opportunities for growth as their companions the possibility of being better citizens in a country without ghettos and fences but civil and solidarity. A fact to be proud of and I never imagined could be a reason for discussion.” According to Pancalli "every discrimination and any choice that tends to separate people is not acceptable in a country that is based on the values of equality of solidarity and respect for every human being. As a disabled person and a man of sport I am happy and proud of how sport has contributed to overcome every diversity and barrier. I believe that today society is ahead of certain unacceptable and retrive proposals.” &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"Before speaking General Vannacci should think": so to the AGI&nbsp; Lieutenant Colonel Gianfranco&nbsp;Paglia>, who lost the use of the legs on July 2, 1993 in the 'battle of the pastifice in Mogadishu in Somalia and for the courage and altruism shown on that occasion was decorated with the Gold Medal to the Military Valor. His story and battle at the "Checkpoint Pasta" also inspired the television film "Le Ali". "With those words Vannacci has shown that he has no knowledge of people with disabilities - said Colonel &nbsp;Paglia&nbsp;- he should go around and really understand what they are and can give. The fact that these words come from a general who wore the stars is really a slap, even towards all the soldiers who by service have lost their physical efficiency". As for Vannacci's candidacy to the Europeans, Paglia said "to be pleased that he has nominated, with the hope that he can no longer return to wearing the uniform because he does not deserve it".
